Parameter.Name: Total Magnetic Field Power
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Total Magnetic Field Power, Sum of the BuBu, BvBv, and BwBw Trace Amplitudes
Parameter.Caveats: This parameter is virtual. It is calculated by calling the function SUM_VALUES with the following input parameters: BuBu, BvBv, BwBw.

Parameter.Name: Total Electric Field Power
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Total Electric Field Power, Sum of the EuEu, EvEv, and EwEw Trace Amplitudes
Parameter.Caveats: This parameter is virtual. It is calculated by calling the function SUM_VALUES with the following input parameters: EuEu, EvEv.

Parameter.Name: Onboard Burst Quality Factor
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Chorus Burst Onboard calculated Quality Factor
Parameter.Caveats: QF is dependant on the Mode being run. This Number is calculated Onboard and can be altered depending on the Waveform of Interest. It is a relative Approximation of Wave Mode Power. The highest QF Bursts are kept over a selectable Interval

Parameter.Name: Five Channel Wave Normal Analysis (WNA) Mode Flag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Five Channel Wave Normal Analysis (WNA) Mode Flag, denotes whether Onboard Wave Normal Analysis is performed
Parameter.Caveats: This Flag is set when the Onboard WNA Program uses the Five-Channel Approximation. E dot B = 0, where the Spin Axis Electric Field Measurement is ignored.

Parameter.Name: Calibrated Waveform Receiver (WFR) Data Flag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Onboard Wave Normal Analysis (WNA) is using Calibrated WFR Data
Parameter.Caveats: Onboard WNA is using calibrated WFR Data

Parameter.Name: Data Flag for Onboard Wave Normal Analysis (WNA) Program Despining
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Onboard Wave Normal Analysis (WNA) Program is despining Data
Parameter.Caveats: Onboard WNA Program is despining Data

Parameter.Name: Gain Attenuator Select Indicator for the W Axis
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Attenuator Select Indicator for the W Axis, 0=OFF
Parameter.Caveats: Attenuator Select Indicator for W Axis. 0 - Off, 1 - On. Switches in a 19 dB Attenuator. Level 2 Data and higher Level Data have the Attenuator Gains folded into the Data to provide correct Science Units.

Parameter.Name: Gain Attenuator Select Indicator for the U and V Axes
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Attenuator Select Indicator for the U/V Axes, 0=OFF
Parameter.Caveats: Attenuator Select Indicator for U and V Axis. 0 - Off, 1 - On. Switches in a 19 dB Attenuator. Level 2 Data and higher Level Data have the Attenuator Gains folded into the Data to provide correct Science Units.

Parameter.Name: Gain Attenuator Select Indicator for Search Coil Magnetometer (SCM)
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Attenuator Select Indicator for the Search Coil Magnetometer (SCM), 0=OFF
Parameter.Caveats: Attenuator Select Indicator for MSC. 0 - Off, 1 - On. Switches in a 19 dB Attenuator. Level 2 Data and higher Level Data have the Attenuator Gains folded into the Data to provide correct Science Units.
